description.narrative:
The project aims to improve vocational training in Burkina Faso. Specifically it aims&nbsp;to improve conditions&nbsp;for the training and social integration of young people at the end of training.
The fact is that once trained, learners are left to themselves. Many are forced to do other activities to the detriment of their basic training; they face the challenges of the professional world. When we take 100 apprentices trained girls, only about 2% manage to find a job.
At the end of the project the main results will be achieved:
-The Ministry of Youth and Employment develops 10 new modules from the non-formal vocational training centers;
-The Ministry of Youth and Employment is committed to ensuring the effectiveness of the systematic teaching of entrepreneurship courses and technical job search throughout training centers non-formal vocational.
The project will be implemented by&nbsp;Association tout pour tous Yennega in the 13 regions of Burkina. The rightsholders/target groups are the centers of non-formal education and youth training in these centers.
The main thematic focus of project is human right spefically right to education. The project will also focus on gender inequalities focusing on girls' access to&nbsp;job said reserved to men only. 
